There are presently no fully validated alternative methods replacing the classical Draize 
in vivo eye irritation test, which is now involving the use of one to three rabbits. Over the 
years, the test method has been subject to refinement and reduction measures, bringing the 
number of animals down from maximum six to maximum three, and involving a number of 
